Bauchi State Governor and 2023 presidential aspirant on the platform of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Bala Mohammed, has declared that it is too late for him to step down for a consensus candidate. He disclosed this on Saturday while speaking to reporters at the ongoing PDP special national convention in Abuja, expressing that it is not feasible for him to just abandon his presidential ambition. The governor said, “Yes, I have been approached but it is too late for me to step down for consensus candidate. -Advertisement- “Yes, I am a product of consensus. Presidency and governorship are issues of consensus but it came very late and it is not feasible for me to just abandon the project, leaving my supporters and Nigerians who look up to me. “So, I am still in the race, I am not stepping down for anybody.”